      "nextButtonText": "I am Ready to Start",
      "nextButtonLocation": "sidebar",
      "instruction": "Imagine you're presenting this visualization to your boss. Write down the text you would use for your speech.",
      "instructionLocation": "sidebar",
      "response": [
        {
          "id": "main-observations-example",
          "prompt": "####  <span style=\"color:red\">Example Response</span> \n",
          "location": "sidebar",
          "type": "longText",
          "minRows": 19,
          "autosize": true,
          "maxRows": 19,
          "required": false,
          "defaultValue": "This line chart shows regional population data from 1950 to 2100. The x-axis shows years in 20-year steps; the y-axis shows population size (millions, M, to billions, G).\n\nIt is clear to see that Asia (the orange line) has the largest population, which is projected to peak a little above 5 billion around mid-century (~2050–2060) and then to decline to about 4.6 billion.\n\nAfrica (blue) shows the strongest growth—rising from a few hundred million in 1950 to almost 4 billion by 2100—almost closing the gap to Asia.\n\n [Example intentionally stops here]\n\nWrite your speech in your own style. You do not need to word things this way: you can be shorter (but not much shorter) or longer; use bullet points or full sentences; reorder points; and choose different phrasing."
        }
      ]
    },
